  • Method Details

    • performService

      public abstract boolean performService​(Role role)
      The performService method is abstract in order to enforce sub-classes to dynamically perform different services when called as part of the command design pattern.

      Parameters:
      role - The role parameter is the wrapper class identity for the user of the program. It contains references to non-package classes.
      Returns:
      boolean The return type determines if the main menu loop with continue functioning.

    • obtainTargetUserAccountNumber

      java.lang.Integer obtainTargetUserAccountNumber​(Role role, java.lang.String instructionForChoosingAccount, java.lang.String fileName)
      The obtainTargetUserAccountNumber method is used to created a menu of accounts belonging to a specific customer. The user specifies which account is desired.

      Parameters:
      role - The role parameter is the wrapper class identity for the user of the program. It contains references to non-package classes.
      Returns:
      Integer Returns the chosen account's number.

    • useUserIDToGetTargetAccount

      java.lang.Integer useUserIDToGetTargetAccount​(Role role, java.lang.String instructionForChoosingAccount, java.lang.String fileName, java.lang.Integer iUserID)
      The useUserIDToGetTargetAccount method reads in all accounts, finds those belonging to the iUserID, displays the accounts, and allows the user to choose one for service.

      Parameters:
      role - The role parameter is the wrapper class identity for the user of the program. It contains references to non-package classes.
      instructionForChoosingAccount - The instructionForChoosingAccount parameter is the instruction given to the user for selecting an account from the displayed menu.
      Returns:
      Integer Returns the chosen account's number.
